<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">Bluebird Inc., a global provider of enterprise mobile devices, has partnered with Teamwork Commerce to launch an RFID integration aimed at how retailers manage inventory. The integration pairs Bluebird's RFR901 RFID scanner with Teamwork Commerce PRO for iPhone, allowing retailers to run inventory counts directly from their Apple devices.</p>

<h2>What the hardware does</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">The RFR901 is an ergonomic scanner designed to be easy to hold during repeated use. It can scan more than 1,300 tags per second at distances of up to 10 meters, with data synchronized instantly across all POS PRO devices running Teamwork Commerce.</p>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">The integration also supports supply chain workflows including purchase receipts and transfer orders, giving retailers streamlined operations across both Teamwork-managed and third-party warehouse systems.</p>

<h2>Why it matters for inventory accuracy</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">Aleksander Martyshko, Sr. Software Mobile Architect at Teamwork Commerce, said: "In today's dynamic retail environment, inventory accuracy is the cornerstone of success. Our partnership with Bluebird will empower retailers with cutting-edge tools to maintain real-time stock visibility."</p>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">Jinoh Kim, CEO of Bluebird Inc., added: "As the retail industry continues to evolve, innovation and precision are key to staying ahead. At Bluebird, we are proud to partner with Teamwork Commerce, a leader in retail technology, to bring our RFID solutions to the market. Together, we are giving retailers the tools they need for inventory accuracy and operational efficiency."</p>

<h2>Built for vertically integrated retailers</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">The integration is designed for vertically integrated and mono-brand retailers, simplifying internal transfers and warehouse operations so brands can focus on customer experience and scaling their business rather than reconciling stock counts by hand.</p>
